    "description": "Toyokumo, Inc. develops and provides cloud services in Japan. It offers Safety Confirmation Service II, a safety confirmation system that enables discussions and instructions in an emergency; NotePM, a service that allows for centralized management of knowledge and know-how; Toyokumo Scheduler, a group scheduler that enables coordination of schedules with external partners; FormBridge, an input to kintone from a web form; and kViewer to create a web page to publish kintone data. The company also provides kMailer, which sends emails to addresses registered in kintone; PrintCreator for output kintone data as a document; DataCollect to aggregate kintone data; and kBackup to back up kintone data. The company was formerly known as Cybozu Startups, Inc. and changed its name to Toyokumo, Inc. in July 2019. Toyokumo, Inc. was incorporated in 2010 and is based in Tokyo, Japan."
